How to Deploy
Using GitHub Pages:
Create a new repository on GitHub.

Push all the files of the project (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) to the repository.

Go to the repository settings, scroll down to the GitHub Pages section, and set the source to the main branch (usually main or master).

Your website will be live at https://github.com/PLP-WebTechnologies/feb-2025-final-project-and-deployment-Mwaniqi26.

Challenges Faced
Responsive Design:

Ensuring the website was responsive on different screen sizes was challenging. I used CSS media queries to adjust the layout and font sizes for smaller screens.

JavaScript Form Validation:

Initially, I faced issues with handling empty fields and properly triggering the validation. Once resolved, the form now provides real-time feedback to users if any fields are left incomplete.

Conclusion
This project helped me reinforce my skills in HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript. By designing a multipage website with basic interactivity and deploying it, I gained valuable experience in web development and deployment using GitHub Pages. The website is fully responsive and works on both mobile and desktop devices, making it accessible to a wide range of users.

